sdp/logs/Verify_T-012_20260416T181925Z_1776386201.log:206:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-17T00:38:26.313Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1776386306313_0","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-012@20260416T181925Z\n\n**Verify Agent:** gemini-3-flash-preview\n**Date:** 2026-04-17\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/music_tracker_runtime.py`\n- `tests/test_music_tracker_runtime.py`\n- `ESCALATIONS.md`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation accurately reflects the requirements. The `ScheduledTrackerEvent` dataclass has been extended with the required sensor fields. Clamping is correctly implemented with the specified bounds:\n- `sensor_tempo_scale` ∈ [0.92, 1.08]\n- `sensor_amp_scale` ∈ [0.80, 1.20]\n- `sensor_brightness` ∈ [-1.0, +1.0]\n\nValues are rounded to 4 decimal places, and warnings are logged when clamping occurs, as verified by `TestSensorClamping`.\n\n## Completeness\nThe task is complete. The scheduler (`schedule_scene` and `schedule_song`) now supports an optional `sensor_fn` to provide real-time modulation and a `delta_track_path` to persist these values. A `replay_sensor_fn` is provided to enable deterministic replay from the persisted delta track, satisfying the requirement for replay capability.\n\n## Consistency\nThe implementation follows established patterns in the codebase, such as using `replace` for dataclass updates and atomic file writes for state persistence (using temporary files and `os.replace`). The naming conventions and module structure are consistent with the `senseweave` package.\n\n## Security\nNo security vulnerabilities or unsafe practices were introduced. File I/O for the delta track is handled safely using Pathlib and atomic replacements. No sensitive information is logged.\n\n## Quality\nThe code quality is high, with clear separation of concerns. The addition of a comprehensive test suite in `tests/test_music_tracker_runtime.py` (36 passing tests) ensures high confidence in the implementation and protects against regressions.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [x] Pre-existing: `my-claw/tools/daemon.py` calls `tg_send(startup_banner)` at line 2461, before `bootstrap_identity()` at line 2464. This is a pre-existing platform-level hardening gap acknowledged in `ESCALATIONS.md` and unrelated to the T-012 music scheduler logic. — severity: minor (pre-existing)\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe core scheduler implementation for the delta track is robust and well-tested. The capability to record and replay expressive modulations is now fully integrated into the `music_tracker_runtime`. Future tasks (like T-037) can now utilize the `delta_track_path` and `replay_sensor_fn` for full performance reproduction.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-012@20260416t181925z-verify.md"}}
