"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-27T07:04:29.841Z\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\" recent commits and the specification for task T-032.\",\"delta\":true}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-27T07:04:29.882Z\",\"tool_name\":\"run_shell_command\",\"tool_id\":\"run_shell_command_1777273469882_0\",\"parameters\":{\"description\":\"Reviewing recent commits and checking for the specification file.\",\"command\":\"git log --oneline -10 && ls specs/t-032@20260427t001208zb-spec.md\"}}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-27T07:04:30.131Z\",\"tool_id\":\"run_shell_command_1777273469882_0\",\"status\":\"success\",\"output\":\"e5ae725 (HEAD -> feat/graceful-degradation) feat(telemetry): extract steady-state cost data per day to CSV [T-032@20260427T001208Zb]\\n5c15925 verify(T-032@20260427T001208Za): PASS\\ne3d49d1 feat(telemetry): document SDP cost model [T-032@20260427T001208Za]\\n5e67663 verify(T-031@20260427T001208Z): PASS WITH NOTES\\n30c1445 feat(generation): wire weekly KL-audit systemd unit and config template [T-031@20260427T001208Z]\\n304a99f verify(T-031@20260427T001208Z): FAIL\\n84a7417 feat(generation): weekly IDyOM LTM KL-divergence audit [T-031@20260427T001208Z]\\n12b54de verify(T-030@20260427T001208Z): PASS\\nf09c5e4 feat(generation): add generation client protocol [T-030@20260427T001208Z]\\n9a40531 verify(T-029@20260427T001208Z): PASS WITH NOTES\\nspecs/t-032@20260427t001208zb-spec.md\"}\n+{\"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-27T07:04:31.966Z\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"I'll read the specification for\",\"delta\":true}\n+{\"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-27T07:04:31.978Z\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\" task T-032 to understand the requirements and expected output.\",\"delta\":true}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-27T07:04:31.999Z\",\"tool_name\":\"read_file\",\"tool_id\":\"read_file_1777273471999_0\",\"parameters\":{\"file_path\":\"specs/t-032@20260427t001208zb-spec.md\"}}\n+{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-27T07:04:32.132Z\",\"tool_id\":\"read_file_1777273471999_0\",\"status\":\"success\",\"output\":\"\"}\n+[AGENT] Elapsed: 12.0s / 30m 0s\ndiff --git a/sdp/telemetry/prompt-review-2026-04-27.md b/sdp/telemetry/prompt-review-2026-04-27.md\nindex e2c0f5b..7aed51c 100644\n--- a/sdp/telemetry/prompt-review-2026-04-27.md\n+++ b/sdp/telemetry/prompt-review-2026-04-27.md\n@@ -1,6 +1,6 @@\n # Prompt Review\n \n-**Generated At:** 2026-04-27T02:37:34.137534+00:00\n+**Generated At:** 2026-04-27T06:05:37.056816+00:00\n **Retry Context Window:** 20\n \n ## Recent Failure Patterns\ndiff --git a/sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cost.csv b/sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cost.csv\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..1672b5e\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cost.csv\n@@ -0,0 +1,8 @@\n+date,runs,input_tokens,output_tokens,cache_creation_tokens,cache_read_tokens,total_cost_usd,models\n+2026-04-08,8,3276,944751,0,0,31.0577,claude-opus-4|fallback\n+2026-04-09,6,2716,983616,0,0,24.3913,claude-opus-4|fallback\n+2026-04-16,67,36035,6916520,0,0,280.6976,claude-opus-4|fallback\n+2026-04-17,38,19196,3046394,0,0,69.4503,claude-opus-4|fallback\n+2026-04-25,32,26989,1786798,0,0,44.0537,claude-opus-4|fallback\n+2026-04-26,48,37799,2895265,0,0,86.9419,claude-opus-4|fallback\n+2026-04-27,30,16565,18094483,0,0,299.6644,claude-opus-4|fallback\ndiff --git a/specs/t-032@20260427t001208zb-spec.md b/specs/t-032@20260427t001208zb-spec.md\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..34eb930\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/specs/t-032@20260427t001208zb-spec.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,100 @@\n+# Task T-032b: Extract steady-state cost data for the last 7+ days\n+\n+## Problem Statement\n+\n+The new `sdp/telemetry/cost-model.md` reference (T-032@a) documents how SDP\n+prices token usage, but operators have no rolled-up cost view. The\n+`telemetry` table in `.sdp/state.db` already records per-task `input_tokens`,\n+`output_tokens`, `cache_creation_tokens`, `cache_read_tokens`, and the\n+`lead_profile_id` of the agent that produced each row, so the data needed\n+for a steady-state cost picture exists. We need a small extractor and a\n+checked-in CSV that summarizes the last 7+ active days of SDP runs by\n+applying the cost-model.md pricing to those telemetry rows.\n+\n+## Technical Approach\n+\n+- Add `promptclaw/sdp_cost.py` exposing:\n+  - `TOKEN_PRICING` — ordered tuple of `(pattern, input_per_m, output_per_m)`\n+    rows mirroring the cost-model.md table, including the `fallback`\n+    sentinel.\n+  - `match_pricing(profile_id: str) -> tuple[str, float, float]` —\n+    case-insensitive substring match against `TOKEN_PRICING`; falls back\n+    to the `fallback` row when nothing matches.\n+  - `call_cost_usd(input_tokens: int, output_tokens: int, profile_id: str) -> float`\n+    applying `(input/1e6 * input_per_m) + (output/1e6 * output_per_m)`.\n+  - `DailyCostRow` dataclass with `date`, `runs`, `input_tokens`,\n+    `output_tokens`, `cache_creation_tokens`, `cache_read_tokens`,\n+    `total_cost_usd`, `models` (sorted unique pricing tiers seen).\n+  - `extract_steady_state_cost(db_path: Path, days: int = 7) -> list[DailyCostRow]`\n+    selecting the `days` most-recent distinct UTC `date(created_at)` values\n+    from `telemetry`, aggregating one row per day, ordered ascending.\n+  - `write_csv(rows: list[DailyCostRow], out_path: Path) -> None` writing\n+    a stable header row plus one CSV row per day.\n+- Add `python -m promptclaw.sdp_cost` CLI thin wrapper supporting\n+  `--db`, `--days`, and `--out` (defaults: `.sdp/state.db`, `7`,\n+  `sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cost.csv`).\n+- Run the CLI once and commit the resulting CSV at\n+  `sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cost.csv`. The CSV is the human-readable\n+  artifact required by the task title; the module is its source of truth.\n+\n+## Edge Cases\n+\n+- The current `telemetry` table contains 7 distinct active days\n+  (2026-04-08, 04-09, 04-16, 04-17, 04-25, 04-26, 04-27) with calendar\n+  gaps. \"Last 7+ consecutive days\" is therefore interpreted as the 7\n+  most recent **active** days; the CSV groups by `date(created_at)` and\n+  the calendar gaps are visible from the date column.\n+- `lead_profile_id` patterns in current data are `claude-opus-4-7-*`,\n+  `claude-opus-4-6-*`, `claude-sonnet-4-6-*`, `gpt-5.4-*`, `gpt-5.5-*`,\n+  `gemini-3.1-*`. Per cost-model.md substring rules,\n+  `claude-opus-4-*` matches `claude-opus-4`, `claude-sonnet-4-*` matches\n+  `claude-sonnet-4`, and the rest fall through to `fallback` ($3/$15).\n+- Empty `lead_profile_id` falls through to `fallback`.\n+- Zero or missing token counts yield `0.0` cost without raising.\n+- A telemetry row's `input_tokens` / `output_tokens` are billed against\n+  the row's `lead_profile_id` only; verify-agent token splits are not\n+  separately recorded in the table and are therefore folded into the\n+  same row, matching the existing cost-summary contract.\n+- `cache_creation_tokens`, `cache_read_tokens`, and `thinking_tokens`\n+  are reported as columns but, per cost-model.md, do not contribute to\n+  `total_cost_usd`.\n+\n+## Acceptance Criteria\n+\n+1. `promptclaw.sdp_cost` exposes `TOKEN_PRICING`, `match_pricing`,\n+   `call_cost_usd`, `DailyCostRow`, `extract_steady_state_cost`, and\n+   `write_csv` with the documented signatures and applies the\n+   cost-model.md pricing table verbatim.\n+   - **VERIFY:** `pytest tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py -q`\n+\n+2. `match_pricing` is a case-insensitive substring match that returns\n+   the cost-model.md tier names (`claude-opus-4`, `claude-sonnet-4`,\n+   `claude-haiku`, `gpt-4o`, `o3`, `codex-mini`, `fallback`) and\n+   `call_cost_usd` matches the cost-model.md formula\n+   (`(in/1e6*in_p) + (out/1e6*out_p)`).\n+   - **VERIFY:** `pytest tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py::test_match_pricing_substring_and_fallback tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py::test_call_cost_usd_matches_cost_model_formula -q`\n+\n+3. `extract_steady_state_cost(db_path, days=7)` returns one\n+   `DailyCostRow` per UTC date for the most recent `days` distinct\n+   active days in the `telemetry` table, ordered ascending by date,\n+   with per-day totals for runs, input/output/cache tokens, USD cost,\n+   and the sorted unique pricing tiers seen.\n+   - **VERIFY:** `pytest tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py::test_extract_steady_state_cost_groups_and_prices_by_day -q`\n+\n+4. `write_csv` writes a stable header\n+   (`date,runs,input_tokens,output_tokens,cache_creation_tokens,cache_read_tokens,total_cost_usd,models`)\n+   followed by one row per day, with `total_cost_usd` formatted to four\n+   decimal places and `models` joined by `|`.\n+   - **VERIFY:** `pytest tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py::test_write_csv_emits_stable_schema -q`\n+\n+5. The CLI `python -m promptclaw.sdp_cost --db <db> --days 7 --out <csv>`\n+   writes the CSV to the requested path and prints the path on stdout.\n+   - **VERIFY:** `pytest tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py::test_cli_writes_csv_and_prints_path -q`\n+\n+6. `sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cost.csv` is committed and contains 7\n+   data rows derived from the live `.sdp/state.db` snapshot.\n+   - **VERIFY:** `python -c \"import csv,pathlib; rows=list(csv.reader(pathlib.Path('sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cost.csv').open())); assert rows[0][0]=='date' and len(rows)==8\"`\n+\n+7. Product-facing change notes mention the new steady-state cost CSV\n+   and extractor.\n+   - **VERIFY:** `grep -n \"steady-state-cost.csv\" CHANGELOG.md`\ndiff --git a/tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py b/tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..d17516b\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py\n@@ -0,0 +1,255 @@\n+\"\"\"Tests for the SDP steady-state cost extractor (T-032@b).\"\"\"\n+\n+from __future__ import annotations\n+\n+import csv\n+import io\n+import sqlite3\n+import subprocess\n+import sys\n+from pathlib import Path\n+\n+import pytest\n+\n+from promptclaw import sdp_cost\n+\n+\n+def _make_telemetry_db(path: Path) -> None:\n+    conn = sqlite3.connect(path)\n+    try:\n+        conn.execute(\n+            \"\"\"\n+            CREATE TABLE telemetry (\n+                telemetry_id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n+                task_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n+                tier TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'T1',\n+                complexity_score INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n+                lead_agent TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',\n+                verify_agent TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',\n+                lead_prompt_template_version TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',\n+                verify_prompt_template_version TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',\n+                lead_profile_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',\n+                verify_profile_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',\n+                lead_model_profile TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n+                verify_model_profile TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n+                duration_seconds REAL NOT NULL DEFAULT 0.0,\n+                outcome TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pass',\n+                retry_count INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n+                gate_results TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '[]',\n+                prompt_length_bytes INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n+                log_size_bytes INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n+                task_category TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',\n+                verification_outcome TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'skip',\n+                input_tokens INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n+                output_tokens INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n+                thinking_tokens INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n+                lint_pass INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n+                test_pass INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n+                regression_detected INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n+                agent TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'claude',\n+                created_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n+                cache_creation_tokens INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n+                cache_read_tokens INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0\n+            )\n+            \"\"\"\n+        )\n+        rows = [\n+            # Two days at the start that should be excluded by days=3 cutoff.\n+            (\"T-A\", \"claude-opus-4-7-high\", 1000, 2000, 0, 0, \"2026-04-01T10:00:00+00:00\"),\n+            (\"T-B\", \"gpt-5.4-xhigh\", 500, 1500, 0, 0, \"2026-04-02T10:00:00+00:00\"),\n+            # Three most-recent active days (selected by days=3).\n+            (\"T-C\", \"claude-opus-4-7-high\", 10_000, 5_000, 100, 200, \"2026-04-25T10:00:00+00:00\"),\n+            (\"T-D\", \"claude-sonnet-4-6-standard\", 4_000, 2_000, 0, 0, \"2026-04-25T11:30:00+00:00\"),\n+            (\"T-E\", \"gpt-5.4-xhigh\", 1_000, 3_000, 0, 0, \"2026-04-26T09:00:00+00:00\"),\n+            (\"T-F\", \"claude-opus-4-7-high\", 0, 0, 0, 0, \"2026-04-26T10:00:00+00:00\"),\n+            (\"T-G\", \"claude-sonnet-4-6-standard\", 2_000, 1_000, 50, 50, \"2026-04-27T08:00:00+00:00\"),\n+        ]\n+        conn.executemany(\n+            \"\"\"\n+            INSERT INTO telemetry (\n+                task_id, lead_profile_id, input_tokens, output_tokens,\n+                cache_creation_tokens, cache_read_tokens, created_at\n+            ) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)\n+            \"\"\",\n+            rows,\n+        )\n+        conn.commit()\n+    finally:\n+        conn.close()\n+\n+\n+def test_token_pricing_table_matches_cost_model_doc() -> None:\n+    by_pattern = {pattern: (in_p, out_p) for pattern, in_p, out_p in sdp_cost.TOKEN_PRICING}\n+    assert by_pattern[\"claude-opus-4\"] == (15.00, 75.00)\n+    assert by_pattern[\"claude-sonnet-4\"] == (3.00, 15.00)\n+    assert by_pattern[\"claude-haiku\"] == (0.80, 4.00)\n+    assert by_pattern[\"gpt-4o\"] == (2.50, 10.00)\n+    assert by_pattern[\"o3\"] == (10.00, 40.00)\n+    assert by_pattern[\"codex-mini\"] == (1.50, 6.00)\n+    assert by_pattern[\"fallback\"] == (3.00, 15.00)\n+\n+\n+def test_match_pricing_substring_and_fallback() -> None:\n+    assert sdp_cost.match_pricing(\"claude-opus-4-7-high\")[0] == \"claude-opus-4\"\n+    assert sdp_cost.match_pricing(\"CLAUDE-OPUS-4-6-extended\")[0] == \"claude-opus-4\"\n+    assert sdp_cost.match_pricing(\"claude-sonnet-4-6-standard\")[0] == \"claude-sonnet-4\"\n+    assert sdp_cost.match_pricing(\"claude-haiku-4-5\")[0] == \"claude-haiku\"\n+    assert sdp_cost.match_pricing(\"gpt-4o-mini\")[0] == \"gpt-4o\"\n+    assert sdp_cost.match_pricing(\"o3-pro\")[0] == \"o3\"\n+    assert sdp_cost.match_pricing(\"codex-mini-latest\")[0] == \"codex-mini\"\n+    # Unknown profiles fall through to fallback.\n+    assert sdp_cost.match_pricing(\"gpt-5.4-xhigh\")[0] == \"fallback\"\n+    assert sdp_cost.match_pricing(\"gemini-3.1-pro-preview-high\")[0] == \"fallback\"\n+    assert sdp_cost.match_pricing(\"\")[0] == \"fallback\"\n+    # Pricing values returned alongside tier name.\n+    tier, in_p, out_p = sdp_cost.match_pricing(\"claude-opus-4-7-high\")\n+    assert (in_p, out_p) == (15.00, 75.00)\n+\n+\n+def test_call_cost_usd_matches_cost_model_formula() -> None:\n+    # Cost-model.md worked example: 10k input + 5k output on claude-sonnet-4 = $0.105.\n+    cost = sdp_cost.call_cost_usd(10_000, 5_000, \"claude-sonnet-4-6-standard\")\n+    assert cost == pytest.approx(0.105)\n+    # claude-opus-4: (10_000/1e6 * 15) + (5_000/1e6 * 75) = 0.15 + 0.375 = 0.525\n+    assert sdp_cost.call_cost_usd(10_000, 5_000, \"claude-opus-4-7-high\") == pytest.approx(0.525)\n+    # Fallback ($3/$15) for unknown profile.\n+    assert sdp_cost.call_cost_usd(10_000, 5_000, \"gpt-5.4-xhigh\") == pytest.approx(0.105)\n+    # Zero tokens => zero cost.\n+    assert sdp_cost.call_cost_usd(0, 0, \"claude-opus-4-7-high\") == 0.0\n+\n+\n+def test_extract_steady_state_cost_groups_and_prices_by_day(tmp_path: Path) -> None:\n+    db_path = tmp_path / \"state.db\"\n+    _make_telemetry_db(db_path)\n+\n+    rows = sdp_cost.extract_steady_state_cost(db_path, days=3)\n+\n+    assert [r.date for r in rows] == [\"2026-04-25\", \"2026-04-26\", \"2026-04-27\"]\n+\n+    by_date = {r.date: r for r in rows}\n+\n+    apr25 = by_date[\"2026-04-25\"]\n+    assert apr25.runs == 2\n+    assert apr25.input_tokens == 14_000\n+    assert apr25.output_tokens == 7_000\n+    assert apr25.cache_creation_tokens == 100\n+    assert apr25.cache_read_tokens == 200\n+    # T-C: opus-4 10k/5k -> 0.525; T-D: sonnet-4 4k/2k -> 0.042.\n+    assert apr25.total_cost_usd == pytest.approx(0.525 + 0.042)\n+    assert apr25.models == [\"claude-opus-4\", \"claude-sonnet-4\"]\n+\n+    apr26 = by_date[\"2026-04-26\"]\n+    assert apr26.runs == 2\n+    # T-E fallback 1k/3k -> 0.048; T-F opus-4 0/0 -> 0.0.\n+    assert apr26.total_cost_usd == pytest.approx(0.048)\n+    assert apr26.models == [\"claude-opus-4\", \"fallback\"]\n+\n+    apr27 = by_date[\"2026-04-27\"]\n+    assert apr27.runs == 1\n+    # T-G sonnet-4 2k/1k -> 0.006 + 0.015 = 0.021.\n+    assert apr27.total_cost_usd == pytest.approx(0.021)\n+    assert apr27.models == [\"claude-sonnet-4\"]\n+\n+\n+def test_extract_steady_state_cost_returns_active_days_only(tmp_path: Path) -> None:\n+    db_path = tmp_path / \"state.db\"\n+    _make_telemetry_db(db_path)\n+\n+    # Asking for more days than exist returns all distinct active days.\n+    rows = sdp_cost.extract_steady_state_cost(db_path, days=99)\n+    assert [r.date for r in rows] == [\n+        \"2026-04-01\",\n+        \"2026-04-02\",\n+        \"2026-04-25\",\n+        \"2026-04-26\",\n+        \"2026-04-27\",\n+    ]\n+\n+\n+def test_write_csv_emits_stable_schema(tmp_path: Path) -> None:\n+    rows = [\n+        sdp_cost.DailyCostRow(\n+            date=\"2026-04-25\",\n+            runs=2,\n+            input_tokens=14_000,\n+            output_tokens=7_000,\n+            cache_creation_tokens=100,\n+            cache_read_tokens=200,\n+            total_cost_usd=0.567,\n+            models=[\"claude-opus-4\", \"claude-sonnet-4\"],\n+        ),\n+        sdp_cost.DailyCostRow(\n+            date=\"2026-04-26\",\n+            runs=1,\n+            input_tokens=1_000,\n+            output_tokens=3_000,\n+            cache_creation_tokens=0,\n+            cache_read_tokens=0,\n+            total_cost_usd=0.048,\n+            models=[\"fallback\"],\n+        ),\n+    ]\n+    out = tmp_path / \"out.csv\"\n+    sdp_cost.write_csv(rows, out)\n+\n+    text = out.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n+    parsed = list(csv.reader(io.StringIO(text)))\n+    assert parsed[0] == [\n+        \"date\",\n+        \"runs\",\n+        \"input_tokens\",\n+        \"output_tokens\",\n+        \"cache_creation_tokens\",\n+        \"cache_read_tokens\",\n+        \"total_cost_usd\",\n+        \"models\",\n+    ]\n+    assert parsed[1] == [\n+        \"2026-04-25\",\n+        \"2\",\n+        \"14000\",\n+        \"7000\",\n+        \"100\",\n+        \"200\",\n+        \"0.5670\",\n+        \"claude-opus-4|claude-sonnet-4\",\n+    ]\n+    assert parsed[2] == [\n+        \"2026-04-26\",\n+        \"1\",\n+        \"1000\",\n+        \"3000\",\n+        \"0\",\n+        \"0\",\n+        \"0.0480\",\n+        \"fallback\",\n+    ]\n+\n+\n+def test_cli_writes_csv_and_prints_path(tmp_path: Path) -> None:\n+    db_path = tmp_path / \"state.db\"\n+    _make_telemetry_db(db_path)\n+    out = tmp_path / \"steady-state-cost.csv\"\n+\n+    result = subprocess.run(\n+        [\n+            sys.executable,\n+            \"-m\",\n+            \"promptclaw.sdp_cost\",\n+            \"--db\",\n+            str(db_path),\n+            \"--days\",\n+            \"3\",\n+            \"--out\",\n+            str(out),\n+        ],\n+        check=True,\n+        capture_output=True,\n+        text=True,\n+        cwd=Path(__file__).resolve().parent.parent,\n+    )\n+    assert str(out) in result.stdout\n+    assert out.exists()\n+    parsed = list(csv.reader(out.open(encoding=\"utf-8\")))\n+    assert parsed[0][0] == \"date\"\n+    assert len(parsed) == 4  # header + 3 days"}
